    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "- Neovim version: NVIM 0.1.5-dev\n- Operating system/version: Ubuntu GNOME 15.10\n- Terminal name/version: Gnome-terminal 3.16.2\n- `$TERM`: xterm-256color\n### Actual behaviour\n\nOnly `magic` and `nomagic` can be set.\n### Expected behaviour\n\nI propose adding the other two options as well and converting `magic` to a string from a boolean that takes:\n- `nomagic`\n- `magic`\n- `very magic`\n- `very nomagic`\n### Why?\n\nI believe that all of the settings should be accessible to the user and be configurable and saveable (meaning I don't have to type /\\v every time). And blackslashitis is bad.\n",
